Sentencas: Silver (Ag) electrocatalysts as cathode layers for low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells (LT-SOFCs) are prepared using an atmospheric pressure plasma jet (APPJ).
Titulo: Atmospheric pressure plasma jet fabricating of porous silver electrocatalyst as a promising approach to the creation of cathode layers of low temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The material characteristics of APPJ-coated silver are observed by an X-ray diffractometer and a field-emission scanning electron microscope.
Titulo: Atmospheric pressure plasma jet fabricating of porous silver electrocatalyst as a promising approach to the creation of cathode layers of low temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The porous cathode films, composed of Ag nanoparticles coated on YSZ electrolytes are observed.
Titulo: Atmospheric pressure plasma jet fabricating of porous silver electrocatalyst as a promising approach to the creation of cathode layers of low temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The porous Ni anodic layer is also prepared via an APPJ process on the other side of the YSZ.
Titulo: Atmospheric pressure plasma jet fabricating of porous silver electrocatalyst as a promising approach to the creation of cathode layers of low temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The values of area specific resistance and conductivities of Ag I YSZ are linearly increased with increasing operating temperatures.
Titulo: Atmospheric pressure plasma jet fabricating of porous silver electrocatalyst as a promising approach to the creation of cathode layers of low temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: High conductivities of 139.6 and 143.2 S/cm are obtained at 550 and 600 degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: Atmospheric pressure plasma jet fabricating of porous silver electrocatalyst as a promising approach to the creation of cathode layers of low temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The exchange current and power density at 600 degrees C are 497.9 mA/cm(2) and 108.4 mW/cm(2), respectively.
Titulo: Atmospheric pressure plasma jet fabricating of porous silver electrocatalyst as a promising approach to the creation of cathode layers of low temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The AC impedance shows the two oxygen pathways, surface and bulk, of Ag electrocatalysts as reflected by the responses at low and high frequencies, respectively.
Titulo: Atmospheric pressure plasma jet fabricating of porous silver electrocatalyst as a promising approach to the creation of cathode layers of low temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Furthermore, LT-SOFCs which consist of cathode' electrolyte' anode are fabricated by APPJ technology in a fast-coating process.
Titulo: Atmospheric pressure plasma jet fabricating of porous silver electrocatalyst as a promising approach to the creation of cathode layers of low temperature solid oxide fuel cells
